Build passes, committed, and pushed. Here's the full audit summary:

## Backend & Security Audit Results

### Authentication (33/33 routes)
All routes verify auth via `createServerSupabaseClient()` + `getUser()` and filter by `tenant_id = user.id`. No cross-tenant data exposure.

### Error Handling
Added try-catch wrappers to 15 routes that were missing them:
- `conversations/[id]`, `lease-summary`, `obligations`, `documents` (GET/DELETE), `documents/[id]/url`, `documents/signed-url`, `article-chunks`, `notifications` (GET/PATCH), `portfolio`, `cam-audit/portfolio`, `critical-dates` (GET/PATCH), `rent-escalation`, `auth/signout`

### Rate Limiting
Created `src/lib/rateLimit.ts` — simple in-memory 3s cooldown per user per route. Added to all 13 AI-powered routes: `chat`, `risk-score`, `cam-audit`, `cam-analysis`, `cam-reconciliation`, `lease-compare`, `lease-summary/generate`, `obligations/generate`, `lease-clauses`, `percentage-rent`, `rent-escalation`, `cam-audit/dispute-letter` (inherited), `stores/[id]/detect-asset-class` (inherited).

### AI JSON Parsing
All AI routes already use `parseAIJson` — no raw `JSON.parse` found.

### Database Query Safety
Added `.limit()` to 7 unbounded queries: `documents` (200), `stores` (100), `team` (100), `portfolio` queries (100-1000), `cam-audit/portfolio` (100), `article-chunks` (50), `conversations/[id] messages` (200).

### Environment Variables
Already handled gracefully in `supabase.ts` with placeholder fallbacks.

### Branding
Zero instances of ClauseIQ/LeaseIQ/Tenora in source code.
